<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="S" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Stab2" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Stab,</orth> vb. 1) to thrust or to kill with the point of a weapon: Lucr. Arg. <bibl n="shak. r3 3.2.89" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 III, 2, 89</bibl> <bibl n="shak. tgv 4.1.51" default="NO" valid="yes">Gent. IV, 1, 51</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mm 4.3.19" default="NO" valid="yes">Meas. IV, 3, 19</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. wt 1.2.138" default="NO" valid="yes">Wint. I, 2, 138</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h4 2.4.160" default="NO" valid="yes">H4A II, 4, 160</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h5 4.5.7" default="NO" valid="yes">H5 IV, 5, 7</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h6 4.1.65" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B IV, 1, 65</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h6 4.1.65" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B IV, 1, 65</bibl> <bibl n="shak. 3h6 2.4.6" default="NO" valid="yes">H6C II, 4, 6</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 3h6 2.6.30" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 6, 30</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 3h6 5.5.53" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 5, 53</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r3 1.2.11" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 I, 2, 11</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r3 1.2.11" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 I, 2, 11</bibl> <bibl n="shak. r3 1.2.11" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 I, 2, 11</bibl> <bibl n="shak. r3 1.3.212" default="NO" valid="yes">I, 3, 212</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r3 1.4.56" default="NO" valid="yes">I, 4, 56</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r3 1.4.56" default="NO" valid="yes">I, 4, 56</bibl> <bibl n="shak. r3 1.4.56" default="NO" valid="yes">I, 4, 56</bibl> <bibl n="shak. r3 3.3.16" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 3, 16</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r3 4.4.63" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 4, 63</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tit 5.2.47" default="NO" valid="yes">Tit. V, 2, 47</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tit 5.2.47" default="NO" valid="yes">Tit. V, 2, 47</bibl> <bibl n="shak. tit 5.2.47" default="NO" valid="yes">Tit. V, 2, 47</bibl> <bibl n="shak. rom 2.4.14" default="NO" valid="yes">Rom. II, 4, 14</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tim 5.1.105" default="NO" valid="yes">Tim. V, 1, 105</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. jc 3.2.157" default="NO" valid="yes">Caes. III, 2, 157</bibl>. <cit><quote>I am --ed with laughter,</quote> <bibl n="shak. lll 5.2.80" default="NO" valid="yes">LLL V, 2, 80</bibl></cit> (== I have side-stitches). Obscene double-meaning: <cit><quote>he --ed me in mine own house,</quote> <bibl n="shak. 2h4 2.1.15" default="NO" valid="yes">H4B II, 1, 15</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>if Caesar had --ed their mothers,</quote> <bibl n="shak. jc 1.2.277" default="NO" valid="yes">Caes. I, 2, 277</bibl></cit>. cf. <bibl n="shak. wt 1.2.138" default="NO" valid="yes">Wint. I, 2, 138</bibl>(?).<lb />2) absol. to make or offer a thrust with the point of a weapon: <cit><quote>--ing steel,</quote> <bibl n="shak. wt 4.4.748" default="NO" valid="yes">Wint. IV, 4, 748</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>he will s.</quote> <bibl n="shak. 2h4 2.1.13" default="NO" valid="yes">H4B II, 1, 13</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. jc 3.2.180" default="NO" valid="yes">Caes. III, 2, 180</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. jc 3.2.180" default="NO" valid="yes">Caes. III, 2, 180</bibl> <bibl n="shak. jc 4.3.20" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 3, 20</bibl>. With <emph>at</emph>: <cit><quote>to s. at half an hour of my life,</quote> <bibl n="shak. 2h4 4.5.109" default="NO" valid="yes">H4B IV, 5, 109</bibl></cit>. In a moral sense, == to mortify, to be extremely cutting: <cit><quote>she speaks poniards, and every word --s,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ado 2.1.255" default="NO" valid="yes">Ado II, 1, 255</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>to say a soldier lies, is --ing,</quote> <bibl n="shak. oth 3.4.6" default="NO" valid="yes">Oth. III, 4, 6</bibl></cit>. cf. <cit><quote>first let my words s. him,</quote> <bibl n="shak. 2h6 4.1.66" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B IV, 1, 66</bibl></cit>; and see <bibl n="shak. 3h6 2.1.98" default="NO" valid="yes">H6C II, 1, 98</bibl>.
<lb />3) to drive, to plunge, to thrust (the weapon as object): <cit><quote>s. poniards in our flesh,</quote> <bibl n="shak. 3h6 2.1.98" default="NO" valid="yes">H6C II, 1, 98</bibl></cit>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>